        "description": {
            "value": "<p><strong>Usage</strong> held in 1 hand</p>\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"pf2-icon\">A</span> Strike</p>\n<hr />\n<p>These spring-loaded metal canisters contain a mixture of chemicals and salts that drain and disintegrate nearby undead creatures.</p>\n<p>A ghost charge gives a +2 item bonus to attack rolls, deals [[/r 3d8]] positive damage and 3 positive splash damage, though as usual for positive damage, this damage harms only undead and creatures with negative healing. A primary target that takes damage from a ghost charge becomes @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Enfeebled]{Enfeebled 2} until the start of your next turn.</p>\n<p>Ghost charges are designed to explode even on contact with a spiritual substance, making them ideal for damaging incorporeal undead.</p>"
        },
